Class SimulationExtensionOnEventContractEnforcementInterceptor

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.palladiosimulator.analyzer.slingshot.simulation.extensions.behavioral.interceptors.AbstractInterceptor
      • org.palladiosimulator.analyzer.slingshot.simulation.extensions.behavioral.interceptors.SimulationExtensionOnEventContractEnforcementInterceptor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Interceptor
    public class SimulationExtensionOnEventContractEnforcementInterceptor
extends AbstractInterceptor
    This class post-intercepts the extension methods in order to enforce the specified contract. This is done by checking the return types of the extension method handler and whether its cardinality matches to the specified cardinality in OnEvent.cardinality().
    Author:
    Julijan Katic

                   throws NoContractDefinitionException,
                          ViolatedContractCardinalityException,
                          ViolatedContractTypeException
        Description copied from interface: Interceptor
        Intercepts the method invocation and is executed afterwards.
        Specified by:
        postIntercept in interface Interceptor
        Overrides:
        postIntercept in class AbstractInterceptor
        Parameters:
        extension - The instance of that class in which the method lies.
        m - The method that will be intercepted.
        args - The arguments that are passed onto the method.
        result - The value returned by the method. If the type of the method is void, this should then be null.
        Throws:
        NoContractDefinitionException - if either the class does not have any OnEvent contract or the specified contract does not belong to a method.
        ViolatedContractCardinalityException - if the contract does not match with the resulting cardinality in ResultEvent.
        ViolatedContractTypeException - if the resulting ResultEvent contains an instance of a type not specified in the contract.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the method has not exactly one argument.
